description:
&lt;p&gt;Following a recent promotion, we are looking to appoint a Team Leader for our Assertive Outreach Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have highly developed clinical leadership skills and expert knowledge in the care of people diagnosed with psychosis and severe mood disorder.. The post holder will lead and provide day to day management in the Assertive Outreach Team reporting to the Recovery Services manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should have a mental health qualification with significant demonstrable post graduate experience in Mental Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be able to engage with service users, families and carers with diverse and often complex needs to ensure meaningful and productive interventions are developed and agreed as well as leading our Multi Disciplinary Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a supportive environment with regular clinical and management supervision and opportunities to develop your clinical and management skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Pat Bran&lt;br /&gt;Job title Team Manager&lt;br /&gt;Email address pat.bran@nhs.net&lt;br /&gt;Telephone number 01908 725167&lt;/p&gt;
